    <p>She became <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="jealous"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(珍惜/爱惜)</code></b> of his esteem, when she could no longer hope to be benefited by it.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She was more <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="alive to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(意识到/注意)</code></b> the disgrace, which the want of new clothes must reflect on her daughter’s nuptials, than to any sense of shame at her eloping and living with Wickham a fortnight before they took place.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He would scarcely be ten pounds a year the loser, by the hundred that was to be paid them, for, what with her <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="board and pocket allowance"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(伙食费和零花钱)</code></b>, and the continual <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="presents in money"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(贴补的钱)</code></b> which passed to her through her mother’s hands, Lydia’s expenses had been very little within that sum.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>To be sure, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="it would have been more for the advantage of conversation"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(更能让人津津乐道)</code></b>, had Miss Lydia Bennet <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="come upon the town (out on the town - 去城里娱乐场所寻欢作乐)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(流落到烟花小巷)</code></b>, or, as the happiest alternative, been secluded from the world, in some distance farm house.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But there was much to be talked of, in marrying her, and the good-natured wishes for her well-doing, which had proceeded before from all the spiteful old ladies in Meryton, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="lost but little of their spirit"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(丝毫不减兴致)</code></b> in this change of circumstances, because with such a husband, her misery was considered certain.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>No sentiment of shame <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="gave a damp"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(挫败)</code></b> to her triumph.</p>
